Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.84,0:01:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.09,0:01:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.49,0:01:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- I beat up on giant monsters\Nand robots more than once,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.42,0:01:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can handle\Ngetting a few signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.98,0:01:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Your chieftain needs you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.60,0:01:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your people need you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, join the fight and\Nhelp us save Haven Academy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.29,0:02:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.61,0:02:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd love to have someone\Nwith your skills on our side!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.19,0:02:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mata!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.49,0:02:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Mata] Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.28,0:02:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Mother] You're not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.08,0:02:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.25,0:02:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.92,0:02:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.86,0:03:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they just sit\Naround and do nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with the White Fang\Ngetting ready to attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.77,0:03:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Because not everyone is like you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.78,0:03:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The Faunus here in\NMenagerie, the ones that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,weren't born on the\Nisland, moved here because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they were tired of fighting, of having to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,struggle constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Menagerie is filled with\Npeople that just want
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be left alone and\Nhere we are, asking them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to put the rest of the\Nworld before themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.53,0:03:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- I guess I never really\Nthought about it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.31,0:03:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- The problem is,\Nwhatever happens at Haven
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.67,0:03:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to affect them\Nwhether they like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If Adam gets his way and\NHaven falls, it's only going
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make things worse for the Faunus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.03,0:03:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.92,0:03:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the guy you used to work with?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.43,0:04:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.10,0:04:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sorry, forget I brought it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.72,0:04:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever met someone\Nand thought to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the personification of this word.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay, well, I remember\Ngetting to know Ruby
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinking, This girl is\Nthe embodiment of purity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, I saw Weiss was defiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yang was strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.52,0:04:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- What am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.53,0:04:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jury's still out on that one,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.45,0:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm leaning towards earnest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.12,0:04:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.49,0:04:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- At first I thought Adam was justice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then I thought he was passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But over time, I realized I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.54,0:04:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't any of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.13,0:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He was spite.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.05,0:05:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not hatred, not rage, spite.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.37,0:05:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't accept equality, only suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.55,0:05:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for what he feels the world did to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.37,0:05:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and his way of thinking\Nis dangerously contagious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what worries me about Ilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.72,0:05:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not like Adam, not yet at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.90,0:05:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't know how long that will last.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.83,0:05:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- She was your friend, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- She was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Her chameleon traits meant\Nshe could pass as human.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.21,0:05:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She could've lived a\Nnormal life if she wanted,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.32,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but she didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.22,0:05:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I always admired that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.11,0:05:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She lost her family in\Na mining accident when
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.93,0:05:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,she was young and she\Njoined the White Fang.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.41,0:05:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Like me, she was more\Nor less trained on the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.31,0:05:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,road alongside other Faunus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.36,0:05:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She learned to survive, to defend herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but as people like Sienna and Adam started
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to gain a following, she\Nbecame more dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.51,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I did too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.95,0:06:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents tried to get\Nme to leave with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.52,0:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but I refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.46,0:06:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I had Adam and Ilia, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.26,0:06:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know we're going to\Nhave to face her eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.87,0:06:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.71,0:06:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Sun] So what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.30,0:06:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm going to try and help\Nher the way you helped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Sun] Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- You showed me that\Nsometimes you need to be there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for a friend, even when\Nthey don't want you to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.85,0:06:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was drowning in guilt and fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.95,0:06:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to push you away,\Nbut you didn't give up on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't give up on Ilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about time I saved\Nmy friends for once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.19,0:06:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] You're really\Ngetting better, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.33,0:06:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.36,0:06:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost dinnertime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.32,0:06:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.45,0:06:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about to call it a night anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, you've never fought before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.67,0:07:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just the occasional small Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.30,0:07:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing like this, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.50,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.84,0:07:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like a natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.32,0:07:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's strange, I've\Nonly had this cane for a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,few weeks, but I feel like\NI've had it for a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.56,0:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Longer, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.72,0:07:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I sound like a crazy person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.30,0:07:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- I mean, uh, yeah, just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But at this pace, you'll\Nbe combat ready in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.85,0:07:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.34,0:07:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] Well, uh, I'll see you upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.69,0:07:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] How do you handle all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.38,0:07:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.45,0:07:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm more scared than I've\Never been in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.71,0:07:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,than I ever thought was possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.94,0:07:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I always knew that I wanted\Nto be more than a farmhand,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.46,0:07:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.02,0:08:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would ask for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- We all went to Beacon because\Nwe wanted to help people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.70,0:08:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us asked for this either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.29,0:08:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to press on and--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- How can you be so confident?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.67,0:08:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,People have tried to kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.25,0:08:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's about to go\Nto war all over again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you okay with any of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- When Beacon fell, I\Nlost two of my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.25,0:08:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Penny Polendina and Pyrrha Nikos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.23,0:08:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know them for very\Nlong, but that doesn't change
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.53,0:08:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that they were two of\Nthe most kind-hearted people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.47,0:08:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have ever met.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But that didn't save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.33,0:09:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pyrrha thought that if\Nthere was even the smallest
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,chance of helping someone then\Nit was a chance worth taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.83,0:09:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of that she\Ndied fighting a battle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.01,0:09:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,she knew she couldn't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.35,0:09:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And Penny was killed\Njust to make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.67,0:09:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.89,0:09:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- I am scared, but not just for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened at Beacon\Nshows that Salem doesn't care
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're standing against her or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll kill anybody and\Nthat scares me most of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Pyrrha, Penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.50,0:09:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be lying if I said\Nthat it didn't hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.57,0:09:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That I didn't think about them\Nevery day since I lost them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.04,0:10:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That I didn't wish I had\Nspent more time with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had been me instead,\NI know they would have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.73,0:10:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,kept fighting too, no\Nmatter how dangerous it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what I choose to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.27,0:10:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To keep moving forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.33,0:10:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon, if we don't hurry,\NNora's gonna eat everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Oscar?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.67,0:10:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't gonna be easy,\Nbut the fact that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.62,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,even trying says a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.66,0:10:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're braver than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.61,0:10:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ozpin] She really is\Nremarkable, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.03,0:10:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.72,0:11:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She must've been one of the\Nbest Huntresses at Beacon, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.33,0:11:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ozpin] (chuckles) In some ways, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But in many others no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She has her quirks, her faults,\Njust like everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But she also possesses something\Nunquantifiable, a spark
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that can inspire others even\Nin the darkest of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- This must be really hard on her too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.98,0:11:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ozpin] It most assuredly is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Fennec] Your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.96,0:11:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Corsac] Are of no significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.52,0:11:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is how High Leader\NTaurus wishes to proceed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then we shall make it so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.59,0:11:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Fennec] Of course, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Still.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.24,0:11:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.77,0:11:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sister Ilia, thank\Nyou for meeting with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.54,0:12:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ilia] How may I be of assistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.84,0:12:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We have wonderful news.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.66,0:12:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ilia] What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.17,0:12:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- We finally received a\Nmessage from the Mistral
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.23,0:12:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam Taurus has claimed his place as the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,High Leader of the White Fang.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.71,0:12:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And Sienna?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Buried with honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The other branches of\Nthe Fang have been given
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the story that was agreed upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.24,0:12:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- A necessary sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.56,0:12:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't forget everything she did for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.57,0:12:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Fennec] Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Corsac] Your maturity\Nand understanding in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.52,0:12:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,regards to this matter is appreciated
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.60,0:12:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is why we've summoned\Nyou here this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.14,0:12:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- The White Fang is experiencing\Na transitional period.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.07,0:12:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- Growth requires change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.07,0:12:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- And change can be painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.79,0:13:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- If it's for the betterment of the Faunus
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.93,0:13:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's a pain we can endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.96,0:13:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's our next mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.01,0:13:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Corsac] Containment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,With the CCT towers still inoperable,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.20,0:13:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the luxury of control\Nover the flow of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.65,0:13:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Fennec] News of Adam's\Nascension has yet to reach
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.89,0:13:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Menagerie, but when it does,\Nthe citizens of Kuo Kuana
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.79,0:13:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will undoubtedly react\Npoorly now that the chieftain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,has spoken out against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.75,0:13:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's my fault the Belladonnas\Nhad any ground to stand on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.48,0:13:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do not concern yourself\Nwith past failures, Ilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.92,0:13:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an opportunity for redemption.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.35,0:13:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you need me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- The Belladonnas are the\Nonly remaining threat to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.89,0:13:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam's assault on Haven Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.14,0:13:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- And so they must be silenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.24,0:13:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Silenced?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Corsac] Like Sienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:13:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They stand in the way of\Ntrue progress for our people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Fennec] We would never put\Nsuch a burden on you alone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.34,0:14:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brothers and sisters\Nwill be at your side,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but your relationship\Nwith their daughter makes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.73,0:14:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you an integral part of this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.13,0:14:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Blake?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.56,0:14:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- We know how close you\Nwere with young Blake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.11,0:14:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest assured, High Leader\NTaurus has requested
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.71,0:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,she be taken alive, but\Nwe cannot risk having her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.00,0:14:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,present to defend her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.40,0:14:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- But, the people of Menagerie--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Will come to understand\Nwhat happens to those
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.25,0:14:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who speak out against the White Fang.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- And will be left\Nwithout a leader until our
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.21,0:14:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,victory is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- A necessary sacrifice, Sister Ilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.87,0:15:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- She's right to worry about the citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.59,0:15:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible they may come\Nto see Ghira as a martyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- It is a risk we must\Ntake for our High Leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.15,0:15:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will not allow them to ruin this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Belladonna name has\Nbrought me nothing, but grief!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.87,0:15:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done well in finding the deserter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.81,0:15:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring her to me, alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.82,0:15:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But not before you've\Nslaughtered her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a promise to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.80,0:15:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- He seems unwell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- He carries with him a tremendous burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.58,0:15:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are we sure he is the one to lead us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.52,0:15:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- For now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We must do what is best for the Faunus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.36,0:15:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.99,0:16:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see to Ghira's messenger?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- He rests beneath the waves\Nalong with his warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.89,0:16:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then all is well.
